<item>
 <title>Description of a Gypsy prepared for rally</title>
 <link>http://assorted.in/rallying/description-a-gypsy-prepared-rally</link>
 <description>&lt;p&gt;I found this nice &lt;a href=&quot;http://youtube.com/watch?v=JIgvtEP70NU&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;video&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/a&gt; showing modifications made in a Gypsy, to prepare it for rallying. The embedding of this video is disabled, so you would have to go to this link to view it.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The add-ons have been described very well by experienced rallyist Ashish Gupta. Here is a quick summary:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Roll Cage to prevent the cabin from collapsing in case of a tumble&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Circuit Breaker used to disconnect all electricals in case of an accident&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Fire Extinguisher&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://assorted.in/rallying/description-a-gypsy-prepared-rally&quot;&gt;read more&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
